The social card of the resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The changes provide for the preservation of the travel allowance in public passenger transport.
From September 24, the procedure for organizing the travel of citizens with a social card of the inhabitant of the Ivanov region is changed.
According to the press service of the Russian government in the Ivanovo region, the changes provide for the preservation of travel allowances in public passenger transport and bring the scheme of mutual calculations on the social card in accordance with the requirements of Federal Law No. 161 "On the national payment system".
The social card of the resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The conditions of its application are changing accordingly.
So, the limit of replenishment is now not set in trips, as before, but in the amount of money, with the preservation of winter and summer periods - in winter not more than 400 rubles, in summer period - not more than 800 rubles per month.
Now, social cardholders will have to keep track of their travel receipts, not the number of remaining trips, but the amount of money left over.
The fare for the citizens is half the fare of the carrier.
The rest of the cost of the trip is covered by the regional budget.
The schedule for replenishing the social card with money remains the same - from the 24th of the previous month to the 23rd of the current month.
The new social card system will have a number of advantages.
For example, it is possible to keep a detailed account of the spending of money on the social map with a penny.
In addition, there is the possibility of returning the money you have already paid but have not spent.
We should also add that the scheme of mutual settlement with carriers is becoming transparent, since now half of the fare is paid by the citizen, and exactly the same amount is reimbursed to the carrier by the budget.
No commission will be charged for credit card deposits.
In his turn, Vasily Silkin, Deputy Head of the Department of Road and Transport of the Ivanovo Region, said that in 2014 more than 33 million trips were made using the social map in the region, in 2015 - almost 25 million trips.
The regional budget provides more than 470 million rubles for the provision of a social card for citizens.
As of September 1, the amount of compensation for these purposes amounted to more than 312 million rubles.
During a 911 call, a teacher confesses to killing his girlfriend.
During the 911 call, a high school professor named Shannon Lamb told police that he had shot his girlfriend and that they needed staff to come to their home.
Lamb pointed out that there was a "dog" in the house who was alive but probably upset, and said that the contact information of the deceased's family members could be found on her phone.
Inside the house, police found the body of Amy Prentiss and a note carelessly handwritten on a white sheet of linen paper: "I'm so sorry, I wish I could take it all back, I loved Amy, and she is the only woman who ever loved me", according to the note, according to authorities, signed by Lamb.
There was no indication that Lamb, who had taught two online courses at Delta State University in Cleveland, Mississippi, had by then driven 300 miles to the university campus, where police believe he shot and killed the highly respected history professor Ethan Schmidt on the doorstep of his office.
Delta State University Police Chief Lynn Buford said that the shooting was reported at 10:18 a.m.
He reported that Lamb made that honest 911 call shortly after.
By the end of the day, the victims will be one more, Lamb killed himself as soon as the police surrounded him.
The day after the school shooting forced students and faculty to hide behind locked doors, law enforcement officials were still trying to piece together the motives behind Lamb's actions.
Information shared by investigators on both sides of the state, as well as students and staff who knew him, helped to paint a portrait of a talented but possibly troubled teacher.
The students said they were looking forward to his class.
Police in Goethe, where Prentiss died, said he had no criminal or violent charges.
Schmidt himself included Lamb in a book he wrote, in which he expressed appreciation for the "wonderful people" he had met in his teaching life.
They both taught at the Faculty of Social Sciences and History, which has 17 faculty members, and many students attended lectures of both.
At the same time, there were some prerequisites for problems.
One student who spoke highly of Lamb, Brandon Beavers, reported that he also seemed anxious and nervous, "as if something were wrong with him".
Another student, Michael Sykes, reported that Lamb told him about his struggles with stress at the end of the 2014-15 school year.
Lamb had earlier asked Delta State University to grant him sick leave, saying he had some health problems.
He's only taught two online courses this year.
Recent changes to university admissions meant that the doctorate Lamb worked so hard for would not guarantee him an automatic teaching position.
University President William LaForge said he knew nothing about the Lamb-Schmidt conflict, but "it was obvious that Mr. Lamb had something on his mind".
These are questions Lamb can no longer answer.
Police raided Lamb's trail after he escaped from campus as he made his way back to Mississippi from Arkansas.
Before he could be arrested, Lamb shot himself with a .38-caliber revolver in the backyard of his home, a mile south of his parents' home in suburban Greenville, Mississippi, Washington County Coroner Mettle Johnson said.
His car with the engine still running was parked on the driveway.
It was not immediately clear why Lamb had come to the house, although Johnson said she believed he knew the people who lived there.
Lamb grew up around there.
Lamb began working at the university, which has 3,500 students in a city with a population of about 12,000, in 2009 and taught geography and pedagogy.
He received his doctorate in pedagogy in the spring of the same year.
One of Lamb's old friends described him as a smart, charismatic and cheerful man.
