Our eyelids are like blinds that protect the eyeball from the many tiny particles that settle on it.
Forgetting to clean our eyelids regularly, we often contribute to the development of blepharitis.
The solution is simple:
Do not rub your eyes with dirty hands, carry a special wet eye dryer.
Clean the edges of the lids at least once or twice a day from the accumulated harmful substances.
