We pushed the reforms forward.
Of course, we lacked the necessary determination and speed, but we acted in an emergency.
The market fell, and there were no potential buyers willing to pay the price the Greek government agreed.
I was the speaker of the parliament at the time, and I managed to get the views of the three parliamentary groups, which were then the majority in the government, together.
