They're victims of the war in Syria, victims of some kind of emergency that happened to them.
This is a matter of profound humanitarian concern and we will take the position that European politicians must take in this new situation.
The EU summit should make a decision, and the United Nations should be involved.
We also need better coordination, more efficient border controls and refugee reception centres.
We must also make effective use of the economic aid we receive from the EU in order to be able to deal with this urgent problem.
Euronews: Mr. Meimarakis, thank you for the interview.
Vangelys Meimarakis: Thank you very much.
