It's all about me.
My European friend, who wants Britain to be interested in maintaining external contacts under the European Union's umbrella - "Don't leave us with France", says Berlin - suggests that the busy ministers and officials in some capitals come to an understanding when it doesn't matter whether we stay or go.
Angela Merkel, Germany's cautious chancellor, is an ally, but she has been in power for 10 years and wants to leave the cabinet before things get worse for her, as they have for her successors Thatcher (11), Mitterrand (14) and Kohl (16).
French President François Hollande faces re-election or replacement in 2017.
