"Review was a fix", and "Britain gained nothing of value from the resumption of negotiations".
Europeans know, to their dismay, what a predator Fleet Street can be, and how skeptical the media moguls are of the EU, unlike the time of Tony Benn's 1975 referendum, which supported our accession in 1973 by a ratio of 2:1.
