This year, the Russian Manager Association's survey "Top 1000 Russian Managers" is published for the 16th time.
As an instrument for assessing the professional reputation of Russian top-level managers, the study summarizes the work of Russian managers for the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of the winners of last year's rankings.
Last year's winners are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate for this year's rating and nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates included in the initial list is invited to nominate up to ten new managers from other companies, who would be advisable to add to the general pool of candidates.
The following heads of the company's functional areas may be nominated: financial director, commercial director, marketing director, personnel director, IT director, public and corporate relations director, director of relations with authorities, director of corporate management.
Each manager proposed by the experts is invited to participate in the rating and is given the opportunity to nominate his management team and up to ten new executives from other companies.
Candidates are nominated on the basis of the Manager Association's industry classifier: information technology, commercial banks, forestry and forestry, machinery, media business, metallurgy, multi-profile holding companies, professional services, communications and telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, trade, transport, financial sector, pharmaceuticals, chemical industry, energy and fuel complex.
Each participant is provided with a login and password to access the website www.top1000.amr.ru, where they can see information about the other participants and can rate their performance according to the criteria proposed for each functional direction.
The rating methodology is based on the principle "The best choose the best": top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
This principle allows for the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at the meetings of the expert commissions.
All candidates for the current year's rating and multiple candidates for the previous years' rating are invited to the face-to-face meetings of the expert commissions.
The Commission is organized according to functional characteristics: the Commission for the approval of the list of senior leaders and eight Commissions for the approval of the heads of functional directions.
At the meetings of the expert commissions it is proposed to approve the submitted lists in alphabetical order (the places are kept strictly according to the internet-evaluation and are closed information until the publication of the rating) or to make up-to-date adjustments according to the reserve list of candidates attached.
The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of "Ъ".
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
