The two mandates of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation are divided between Vladimir Bulanov and the Deputy of the State Duma Alexander Tarnaev.
The three mandates of the "Just Russia" are given to Alexander Razumovsky, Igor Bogdanov and Mikhail Shalugin.
Now, within five days, these candidates must decide whether they will serve as deputies in the city duma: in case of rejection of the mandate, it goes to the next candidate on the party list.
