Xi calls for opening up the economy to the world
The economy must become more open to the world to stimulate growth, President Xi Jinping said Tuesday in an address to the task force on reform leadership.
"China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop an open-door policy", he said, addressing the participants of the 16th meeting of the Central Leadership Group Committee on Comprehensive Deepening of Reforms.
According to him, the expansion of openness and deepening of reforms will give the economy a new impetus and vitality and provide a new space for economic development.
The leading group adopted a number of directives, including regulating investor access to the market, changing the rules on border control, encouraging state-owned enterprises (SOEs) to attract private capital and reviewing the system of registration of residents.
According to the statement, a list of sectors of the economy and production that are not available for investment will be compiled.
The system will be gradually repaired through trial programs.
This is an important step, as it will give the market a more significant role in allocating resources, ensuring legality in business and increasing openness, the statement said.
The government will also ease controls on the powers it grants to companies, thereby ensuring that companies will run their own businesses.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions to master new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to enhance local growth.
More areas will be open to private investors to increase the openness of state-controlled sectors of the economy.
"The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of foreign-funded companies and provide them with better conditions", the statement said.
The application process for permanent residence permits for foreigners, or "green cards", will be further simplified by streamlining the requirements and simplifying the application process itself.
The meeting also discussed the rights of lawyers and the training of professional judges and prosecutors.
According to the official report released after the meeting, Prime Minister Li Keqiang and Ministers Liu Yunsheng and Zhang Gaoli were also present.
